You will be given an array and a limit value. You must check that all values in the array are below or equal to the limit value. If they are, return true. Else, return false.

You can assume all values in the array are numbers.


//We need to return a boolean for if the highest value in the array is below or eual to the limit value.
//We can spread the array into Math.max() to get the largest value and use a comparison operator for implicit return. 



function smallEnough(a, limit){
  
  return Math.max(...a) <= limit;

}

console.log(smallEnough([66, 101], 200))
